  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>IMG Global is the best choice for budget-conscious expats who want solid coverage without premium prices.</strong> The 50% deductible waiver for care outside the US is a unique feature that makes high-deductible plans genuinely practical. Their 4.6/5 Trustpilot rating reflects real customer satisfaction.
  </p>
  <p>
    However, IMG isn't for everyone. If you need fast claims processing, extensive direct billing, or premium customer service, you'll be happier with Cigna or BUPA despite the higher cost. And the 3-day free look period and inability to lower deductibles at renewal require careful initial planning.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Bottom line:</strong> For value-focused expats living outside the US, IMG offers excellent coverage at competitive prices. The deductible waiver alone can save hundreds per claim.
